{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"df05cc95-f667-4843-bdeb-280d65e7b770","content":"\n\nHere's what to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Update `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v4.6.0+** (you already have this).\n   - Add `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` if not present.\n   - Keep `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`.\n\n2. **Add an MSBuild property** in your `.csproj` (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable the test platform in the adapter** — add to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingPlatform>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   The adapter (4.6.0+) bridges NUnit to Microsoft.Testing.Platform automatically when those properties are set.\n\n**Optional but recommended:**\n- Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` once fully migrated (it's only needed for VSTest).\n- Add `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` or other extensions if you need TRX output or other features.\n\nNo code changes to your `[Test]` methods are required — only project file changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"29345c0e-0d5d-4b98-bf9b-7c93ddf59255","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":415},"id":"e32491eb-393e-4692-aead-49eab6f51b8d","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:39:19.491Z","parentId":"907e07cb-ace9-492d-8cf4-83899473fc37"}
